#MEM id=pletor-agent source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/workflow/pletor-agent/SKILL.md
M|pletor-agent|name: pletor-agt
M|pletor-agent|description: >-
M|pletor-agent|Use this skill whenever the user wants to run, trigger, or interact with a Pletor AI agt via the Pletor Public API. Triggers include: calling a Pletor agt, submitting a job to Pletor, running image/vi
M|pletor-agent|version: 1.0.0
M|pletor-agent|platforms: []
M|pletor-agent|metadata:
M|pletor-agent|hermes:
M|pletor-agent|tags: [coo, operations, workflow, planning, sprint, milestones, process, automation]
M|pletor-agent|This skill handles end-to-end interaction with the Pletor Public API:
M|pletor-agent|discovering agents, uploading assets, creating runs, polling for completion,
M|pletor-agent|and downloading outputs.
M|pletor-agent|**Base URL:** `https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1`
M|pletor-agent|**Auth header:** `X-Api-Key: <user's API key>`
M|pletor-agent|Ask the user for their Pletor API key if it hasn't been provided. Never hardcode or guess it.
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|X-Api-Key: <USER_API_KEY>
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|If the user hasn't specified an agt ID, list available agents and let them choose:
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/agents/" | jq .
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|To filter by visibility or tag:
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/agents/?visibility=PUBLIC&tags=social_media" | jq .
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|To fetch a specific agt's details (inputs/outputs schema):
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/agents/<agent_id>" | jq .
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|The rsp includes:
M|pletor-agent|- `id` — the agt UUID needed to create a run
M|pletor-agent|- `inputs[]` — each with `id`, `type` (`text_input` or asset input), and `description`
M|pletor-agent|- `outputs[]` — what the agt produces (e.g. images, video)
M|pletor-agent|- `estimated_cost` — cost in credits
M|pletor-agent|**Always inspect the agt's `inputs` before building the run payload.**
M|pletor-agent|If any input has type `asset` (e.g. product photo, logo), upload the file first:
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -X POST \
M|pletor-agent|-H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|-F "file=@/path/to/local/file.jpg" \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/assets/upload" | jq .
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|The rsp returns an `id` (asset UUID). Store it — you'll reference it in the run payload.
M|pletor-agent|POST to `/runs/` with the agt ID and all required inputs:
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -X POST \
M|pletor-agent|-H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|-H "cnt-Type: application/json" \
M|pletor-agent|-d '{
M|pletor-agent|"agent_id": "<agent_id>",
M|pletor-agent|"inputs": [
M|pletor-agent|{
M|pletor-agent|"id": "<input_id_for_text>",
M|pletor-agent|"value": "Your text prompt here"
M|pletor-agent|},
M|pletor-agent|{
M|pletor-agent|"id": "<input_id_for_asset>",
M|pletor-agent|"value": {
M|pletor-agent|"asset_ids": ["<asset_uuid>"]
M|pletor-agent|}
M|pletor-agent|}
M|pletor-agent|]
M|pletor-agent|}' \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/runs/" | jq .
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|**Input format rules:**
M|pletor-agent|- Text inputs: `"value": "<string>"`
M|pletor-agent|- Asset inputs: `"value": { "asset_ids": ["<uuid>", ...] }`
M|pletor-agent|- Use the `id` from the agt's `inputs[]` array — not the agt ID itself
M|pletor-agent|The rsp returns a `run_id`. Store it for polling.
M|pletor-agent|Poll until `status` is `"completed"` (or `"failed"`):
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|while true; do
M|pletor-agent|RESULT=$(curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/runs/<run_id>")
M|pletor-agent|STATUS=$(echo $RESULT | jq -r '.status')
M|pletor-agent|echo "Status: $STATUS"
M|pletor-agent|if [ "$STATUS" = "completed" ] || [ "$STATUS" = "failed" ]; then
M|pletor-agent|echo $RESULT | jq .
M|pletor-agent|break
M|pletor-agent|fi
M|pletor-agent|sleep 5
M|pletor-agent|done
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|Recommended poll interval: 5 seconds. Stop on `completed` or `failed`.
M|pletor-agent|Extract asset IDs from the completed run rsp, then download each output:
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|ASSET_IDS=$(echo $RESULT | jq -r '.outputs[].asset_ids[]')
M|pletor-agent|for ASSET_ID in $ASSET_IDS; do
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/assets/$ASSET_ID/download" \
M|pletor-agent|-o "output_$ASSET_ID.jpg"
M|pletor-agent|echo "Downloaded: output_$ASSET_ID.jpg"
M|pletor-agent|done
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|Alternatively, retrieve metadata first to get the filename:
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|"https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1/assets/<asset_id>" | jq .
M|pletor-agent|```
M|pletor-agent|| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
M|pletor-agent||---|---|---|
M|pletor-agent|| `/agents/` | GET | List all agents |
M|pletor-agent|| `/agents/{agent_id}` | GET | Get agt details + input schema |
M|pletor-agent|| `/assets/` | GET | List all assets |
M|pletor-agent|| `/assets/upload` | POST | Upload file (multipart/form-data) |
M|pletor-agent|| `/assets/{asset_id}` | GET | Get asset metadata |
M|pletor-agent|| `/assets/{asset_id}/download` | GET | Download file |
M|pletor-agent|| `/runs/` | POST | Create and start a run |
M|pletor-agent|| `/runs/` | GET | List all runs |
M|pletor-agent|| `/runs/{run_id}` | GET | Get run status and results |
M|pletor-agent|| `/runs/{run_id}` | DELETE | Cancel an ongoing run |
M|pletor-agent|- **401**: Invalid or missing API key — double-check `X-Api-Key` header
M|pletor-agent|- **404**: agt or asset ID not found — verify UUIDs from discovery step
M|pletor-agent|- **422**: Invalid input — re-check the agt's required `inputs` schema
M|pletor-agent|- **run status = "failed"**: Surface the error message from the run rsp to the user
M|pletor-agent|```bash
M|pletor-agent|export PLETOR_API_KEY="your-key-here"
M|pletor-agent|BASE="https://api.pletor.ai/api/public/v1"
M|pletor-agent|AGENT_ID="uuid-of-your-agt"
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" "$BASE/agents/$AGENT_ID" | jq '.inputs'
M|pletor-agent|RUN=$(curl -s -X POST \
M|pletor-agent|-H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|-H "cnt-Type: application/json" \
M|pletor-agent|-d "{\"agent_id\": \"$AGENT_ID\", \"inputs\": [{\"id\": \"<input_id>\", \"value\": \"A sunset over Paris\"}]}" \
M|pletor-agent|"$BASE/runs/")
M|pletor-agent|RUN_ID=$(echo $RUN | jq -r '.id')
M|pletor-agent|while true; do
M|pletor-agent|STATUS=$(curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" "$BASE/runs/$RUN_ID" | jq -r '.status')
M|pletor-agent|[ "$STATUS" = "completed" ] && break
M|pletor-agent|sleep 5
M|pletor-agent|done
M|pletor-agent|curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" "$BASE/runs/$RUN_ID" \
M|pletor-agent|| jq -r '.outputs[].asset_ids[]' \
M|pletor-agent|| xargs -I{} curl -s -H "X-Api-Key: $PLETOR_API_KEY" \
M|pletor-agent|"$BASE/assets/{}/download" -o "result_{}.jpg"
M|pletor-agent|```